headline: Why Molina Healthcare (MOH) Is Down 6.3% After Slashing Guidance and Revealing Higher Medical Costs
summary: In October 2025, Molina Healthcare reported third quarter results showing revenue growth to US$11.48 billion but a significant decline in profitability due to higher medical costs, and also completed a US$499.99 million share repurchase. This series of disclosures, including the downward revision of full-year earnings guidance and ongoing class action lawsuits, has raised questions about the company's ability to manage persistent cost pressures in its Marketplace business. We will examine...
